      <hedline>
        <hl1>Alone at the Top</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Philip Lawton letter disputes Roger Lowenstein's August 27 profile of Sanford I Weill (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Perhaps writers for your magazine should not be their subject's houseguests. For perspectives other than those of Weill, his family and his well-paid circle of sycophants, talk to some ordinary people, like the former Travelers employees forced into early retirement (at best) or the Citigroup operations staff struggling to get more and more work done under relentless pressure to cut costs.</p>
        <p>Philip Lawton  Westfield, N.J.</p>
      </block>
